0us%20apart%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20but%20these%20days%2C%20the%20differences%20are%20slightly%20more%20apparent%20%E2%80%94%20my%20face%20is%20rounder%2C%20and%20Aimee's%20hair%20is%20shorter%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ba023e15-4a75-47c3-b5dd-ec7b5ec39130%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20would%20switch%20classes%20in%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20get%20bombarded%20with%20questions%2C%20and%20usually%20I%20love%20people's%20interest.%20Sometimes%2C%20though%2C%20people's%20comments%20can%20be%20insensitive.%20I've%20been%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BDoes%20your%20sister's%20nose%20go%20up%20like%20yours%20does%3F%26quot%3B%20Strangers%20sometimes%20point%20out%20a%20perceived%20flaw%20to%20demonstrate%20they%20can%20tell%20the%20difference.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20school%2C%20though%2C%20we%20played%20upon%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextreme-sisters-worlds-most-identical-twins-australia-share-fiance-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeing%20confused%20with%20each%20other%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20At%20the%20teachers'%20request%2C%20I%20wore%20yellow%20ribbons%20to%20school%2C%20and%20Aimee%20wore%20blue.%20Most%20days%2C%20we%20swapped%20our%20ribbons%20so%20we%20had%20one%20of%20each%20color%2C%20and%20then%20we%20could%20swap%20classes.%20We%20played%20to%20our%20separate%20strengths%3A%20I%20took%20Aimee's%20Japanese%20and%20music%20exams%2C%20and%20she%20took%20my%20tennis%20exam%20for%20me.%20Teachers%20could%20only%20tell%20us%20apart%20by%20our%20ribbons%20or%20our%20backpacks.%20They%20had%20no%20idea%20we%20bluffed%20for%20each%20other.%20I%20don't%20think%20even%20our%20parents%20knew.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22586%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Identical%20twins%20as%20kids%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e402a2cc993f9955cf9ccf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Charlwood%20and%20her%20sister%20Aimee%20would%20wear%20different%20color%20bows%20in%20their%20hair.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Sarah%20Charlwood%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2016%2C%20we%20both%20went%20to%20cadet%20camp%2C%20but%20Aimee%20went%20home%20sick%20after%20the%20first%20night.%20Within%20two%20hours%20of%20her%20departure%2C%20I%20was%20standing%20at%20a%20phone%2C%20calling%20her.%20It%20felt%20too%20bizarre%20not%20having%20her%20there%20to%20talk%20to.%20She%20moved%20to%20England%20after%20university%2C%20and%20we%20emailed%20and%20texted%20every%20single%20day.%20It%20was%20during%20that%20time%20that%20I%20began%20to%20get%20more%20accustomed%20to%20not%20spending%20all%20my%20time%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e966ce4b-14c1-439c-8999-cfbf4ffee003%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20share%20many%20interests%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20commonly%2C%20we%20get%20asked%20about%20boyfriends%20and%20if%20we%20like%20the%20same%20guys%3B%20(no).%20We've%20never%20gone%20after%20the%20same%20guy%2C%20but%20I%20did%2C%20at%20my%20sister's%20request%2C%20break%20up%20with%20her%20boyfriend%20for%20her%20once%20at%20school.%20He%20didn't%20realize%20it%20was%20actually%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20do%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fidentical-twin-comparison-live-apart-separate-bond-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshare%20many%20other%20tastes%20and%20interests%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20share%20a%20Spotify%20playlist%20and%20an%20Instagram%20reel%20list%20folder.%20We%20read%20the%20same%20books%2C%20and%20have%20the%20same%20food%20preferences%20(we%20both%20dislike%20marzipan).%20We%20recently%20discovered%20our%20favourite%20book%20is%20the%20same.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20parts%20about%20being%20an%20identical%20twin%20is%20sharing%20a%20wardrobe%20%E2%80%94%20we%20genuinely%20have%20the%20same%20style%20and%20like%20and%20share%20the%20exact%20same%20clothes.%20If%20she%20buys%20a%20%24100%20skirt%2C%20it's%20really%20only%20%2450%20because%20we%20both%20get%20to%20wear%20it%20on%20rotation.%20We%20never%20owe%20each%20other%20money%20%E2%80%94%20we%20take%20turns%20buying%20things%2C%20including%20dinners.%20I'll%20see%20her%20at%20least%20two%20to%20three%20times%20a%20week.%20We%20never%20argue.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b420d471-d657-4362-9c61-fdbff742dc70%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20love%20having%20an%20identical%20twin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20often%20say%20the%20most%20similar%20thing%20about%20us%20is%20the%20way%20we%20talk%20%E2%80%94%20the%20way%20we%20move%20our%20hands%20and%20our%20heads%20at%20the%20same%20time%20when%20telling%20a%20story.%20We%20do%20sometimes%20finish%20each%20other's%20sentences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20common%20question%20is%20whether%20we're%20telepathic.%20Eerie%20things%20do%20often%20happen.%20Recently%2C%20I%20Googled%20what%20to%20wear%20to%20an%20Olivia%20Rodrigo%20concert.%20I'd%20just%20typed%20it%20in%20when%20Aimee%20called%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20just%20bought%20you%20an%20Olivia%20Rodrigo%20shirt%20from%20Target.%26quot%3B%20We've%20also%20had%20things%20like%20randomly%20having%20teeth%20out%20on%20the%20same%20day%20when%20she%20was%20overseas.%20It's%20hard%20to%20say%20what's%20just%20a%20coincidence.%20I'd%20say%20we're%20in%20sync%20because%20we%20spend%20so%20much%20time%20together%2C%20but%20not%20telepathic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22942%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Identical%20twins%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e403555dbc4fd10daa43eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221262%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Charlwood%20and%20her%20sister%20Aimee%20share%20