00s-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETesla's%20first%20Roadster%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20only%20been%20released%20a%20few%20years%20prior.%20Those%20same%20components%20%E2%80%94%20batteries%2C%20inverters%2C%20and%20silicon%20carbide%20switches%20%E2%80%94%20made%20electric%20propulsion%20possible%20for%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20sense%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20were%20inspired%20by%20toys.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-airline-world-has-a-tiny-secret-2015-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EModel%20airplanes%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20transforming%20thanks%20to%20better%20batteries%20and%20motor%20controllers.%20It%20was%20the%20same%20principle%2C%20just%20scaled%20up.%20The%20question%20was%3A%20%26quot%3BCan%20these%20technologies%20be%20applied%20to%20larger%20aircraft%20safely%3F%26quot%3B%20Joby%20figured%20this%20out%20early%20on%2C%20and%20it's%20what%20we've%20been%20working%20on%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20there%20something%20you%20believed%20early%20on%20that%20you%20no%20longer%20believe%20today%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20day%20one%2C%20we%20believed%20electric%20propulsion%20could%20make%20aircraft%20quieter%2C%20more%20reliable%2C%20and%20cheaper%20to%20operate.%20We're%20doing%20that%20now.%20What's%20evolved%20is%20the%20business%20model%2C%20whether%20this%20would%20be%20a%20personal%20aircraft%20or%20an%20air%20taxi%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20had%20a%20moment%20where%20you%20realized%20this%20was%20no%20longer%20speculative%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it's%20real%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETotally.%20I%20had%20that%20moment%20several%20weeks%20ago%20at%20an%20event%20where%20we%20were%20showing%20some%20of%20our%20technology.%20We're%20no%20longer%20convincing%20people%20that%20this%20is%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20from%20Zee%20to%20Uber%20is%20a%20big%20shift.%20What%20was%20it%20like%20trying%20to%20bring%20this%20transformative%20mode%20of%20transport%20to%20Uber%2C%20a%20massive%20ride-hailing%20company%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20big%20shift%2C%20but%20it%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20sense.%20At%20Uber%2C%20the%20team%20was%20small%20but%20had%20a%20clear%20and%20ambitious%20product%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber's%20focus%20was%20not%20on%20the%20hardware%2C%20vehicle%20engineering%20side%20of%20things.%20We%20weren't%20developing%20a%20vehicle.%20We%20had%20some%20concept%20vehicles%20that%20we%20developed%2C%20but%20the%20whole%20idea%20was%20to%20get%20others%20to%20develop%20the%20vehicles.%20And%20we%20provided%20the%20overarching%20business%20case%20and%20the%20product%20vision%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20of%20how%20this%20could%20all%20be%20woven%20together%20into%20a%20service%20that%20consumers%20would%20want%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20were%20the%20challenges%20and%20the%20hardest%20part%20of%20running%20Elevate%20inside%20Uber%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20was%20holding%20a%20clear%2C%20ambitious%20vision%20for%20a%20technology%20most%20people%20thought%20was%20still%20science%20fiction.%20The%20tech%20was%20real%2C%20but%20the%20world%20wasn't%20quite%20ready%20to%20believe%20it.%20We%20had%20to%20cast%20a%20vision%20that%20felt%20tangible%20and%20make%20people%20see%20how%20it%20could%20actually%20fit%20into%20their%20daily%20lives.%20That%20was%20both%20the%20most%20challenging%20and%20the%20most%20exciting%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20anything%2C%20there%20were%20pros%20and%20cons.%20But%20overall%2C%20the%20Elevate%20experience%20was%20really%20good.%20Uber%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20credibility%20in%20transportation%2C%20and%20that%20helped%20us%20build%20the%20vision%20and%20bring%20people%20together.%20The%20Elevate%20Summits%20we%20ran%20were%20pivotal%20%E2%80%94%20they%20catalyzed%20the%20industry.%20I%20think%20they%20helped%20spur%20the%20overall%20amount%20of%20investment%20and%20excitement%20that%20pushed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-the-aviation-industry-is-excited-about-flying-taxis-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EeVTOL%20technology%20forward%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20paint%20me%20a%20vivid%20picture%20of%20what%20a%20Joby%20trip%20will%20look%20like%20for%20a%20customer%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20someone%20in%20lower%20Manhattan%20or%20the%20West%20Side%20of%20Manhattan%20who's%20traveling%20for%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20he's%20running%20late%2C%20maybe%20he%20just%20wants%20to%20have%20a%20seamless%2C%20stress-free%20experience%20going%20to%20the%20airport%20on%20a%20Delta%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20open%20the%20Uber%20app%20and%2C%20instead%20of%20selecting%20UberX%20or%20Uber%20Black%2C%20they%20choose%20the%20Joby%20option%20directly%20within%20the%20Uber%20app.%20A%20car%20takes%20them%20to%20the%20West%2030th%20Street%20heliport.%20The%20system%20sequences%20arrivals%20so%20that%20a%20few%20passengers%20arrive%20together.%20They%20all%20flow%20through%20a%20lounge%2C%20where%20we%20also%20operate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelicopter-manhattan-to-jfk-in-5-minutes-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlade%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%20Joby%20recently%20acquired%2C%20and%20board%20the%20aircraft.%20In%20seven%20minutes%2C%20after%20an%20amazing%20view%20and%20stress-free%20experience%2C%20you%20land%20right%20near%20the%20terminal%20at%20JFK%20and%20walk%20right%20in%20to%20go%20through%20security%20and%20get%20on%20your%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20seamless%20and%20stress-free.%20You%20can%20experience%20a%20version%20of%20this%20through%20Blade%20in%20New%20York%2C%20but%20helicopters%20are%20more%20expensive%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20people%20are%20still%20skeptical.%20We've%20seen%20cycles%20of%20hype%20and%20disappointment.%20Why%20is%20this%20moment%20different%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E